    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n2024" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">γέρων</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">οντος</span>, voc. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">γέρον</span>:
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">old man</span> (senex), and specially, mostly in pl.,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">elders</span>, members of the council (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">βουλὴ γερόντων</span>), cf. Lat. senator.—As adj., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πατὴρ γέρων</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            1.358</span></i>, neut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">γέρον σάκος</span>,
            <i><span class="en">Od. 22.184</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
